<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:07PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Lewis
and Clark and western Teton Counties through 630 PM MDT...
At 607 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 27
miles west of Choteau, moving north at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain, winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Lewis
and Clark and western Teton Counties.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
